headline.main: Personal Health; Updating the annual checkup: what to keep in mind

docs.lead_paragraph: ROBERT, 44, was due for his annual physical. As the day neared, he became increasingly apprehensive. He hated being "pummeled and poked" by the doctor and his instruments. He walked into the office thinking; "Why am I doing this? I feel perfectly fine. It's a waste of time and money."
